last_episode_to_air.name: A Trip to Japan: Jaleel White & Kym Whitley
last_episode_to_air.overview: Lisa welcomes Jaleel White and Kym Whitely to an evening of Japanese culinary delights - including a blind taste test, Vanderpump vodka bowling, and loads of sake. Kym's been flirting with Jaleel since they were both starting out and she's still after "the softest lips in Hollywood."

name: Overserved with Lisa Vanderpump
overview: Lisa invites viewers to her extravagant garden at Villa Rosa for an al fresco evening full of unexpected surprises and revealing moments, as she hosts two to three celebrity guests for an unforgettable night full of cocktails, games, and delicious feasts crafted entirely by Lisa herself.

episodes.name: An Evening in Provence: Lance Bass & Vivica A. Fox
episodes.overview: Lisa transports her best friend Lance Bass and actress Vivica A. Fox to the South of France with a Provence-themed party, and serial pranker Lance gets a taste of his own medicine.

episodes.name: A Tuscan Feast: Joel Mchale & Cheryl Hines
episodes.overview: Lisa creates an al fresco Tuscan feast for Italian-born Joel McHale and actress Cheryl Hines. Lisa playfully confronts Joel about things he's said about her in the past.

episodes.name: Diva Tea: Iggy Azalea & Trixie Mattel
episodes.overview: Lisa throws a proper English Tea with some very improper conversation as Iggy Azalea and Trixie Mattel share tales of red carpet underwear fails, one-night stands, and a famous baby daddy.

episodes.name: Cabo Fiesta: Tori Spelling & Jeff Lewis
episodes.overview: Lisa recreates her favorite moments from years of vacationing in Mexico with a night of margaritas, seafood, surprise secrets and wild dares with Tori Spelling and Jeff Lewis.

episodes.name: A Night in Morocco: Jeannie Mai & Meagan Good
episodes.overview: Things get wild on the Villa Rosa dance floor when Lisa welcomes Jeannie Mai and Meagan Good to her home for an evening of Moroccan inspired food, drink and dares - with a few surprise guests via Facetime.

episodes.name: Ladies Who Brunch: Anna Camp & Lala Kent
episodes.overview: Lisa hosts a decadent weekend brunch for her busy friends--a very candid Anna Camp and a very pregnant Lala Kent--and we'll learn why you don't want to cross any of these ladies.

episodes.name: Traditional English Roast: Mario Lopez & Sheryl Underwood
episodes.overview: Lisa brings London to Beverly Hills with an English Roast dinner for dear friend Mario Lopez and the hilarious Sheryl Underwood. The evening gets wild with Ros√© Pong, Spotted Dick (that's a thing), and some roasting of the host courtesy of Sheryl.

episodes.name: Very Vanderpump: Jim Jefferies & James Kennedy
episodes.overview: Lisa rolls out the best of signature Vanderpump style, decor and food for a reformed James Kennedy and the outrageous Jim Jefferies. It's all about the (lobster) pasta!

episodes.name: Go Greek: Steve-O and Margaret Cho
episodes.overview: Lisa transforms her olive grove for a trip to Greece - complete with a ten-dish feast and an Olympic game. Fearless guests Steve-O and Margaret Cho serve up unexpected moments, like an impromptu BDSM lesson and highly inappropriate temporary tattoos.

episodes.name: Beverly Hills Comfort Food: Heather and Terry Dubrow & Loni Love
episodes.overview: Lisa proves the best things in life aren't always the fanciest, as she treats Heather, Dr. Terry Dubrow and comic Loni Love to a night of indulgent comfort food, decadent drinks and even a 20-foot beer bong -- filled with champagne, of course.

episodes.name: Back to Ibiza: Gabriel Iglesias & Cheryl Burke
episodes.overview: Dancing with the Stars Cheryl Burke and comedian Gabriel "Fluffy" Iglesias join Lisa in celebrating her love of the food and culture of Ibiza, Spain--the vibrant, island resort where she and Ken once owned a home.
